org.apache.logging.log4j
Interface Logger

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractLogger, AbstractLoggerWrapper, SimpleLogger, StatusLogger
public interface Logger

This is the central interface in the log4j package. Most logging operations, except configuration, are done through this interface.

Troublesome:
See LOG4J2-16.

entry

void entry()
Logs entry to a method.

entry

void entry(Object... params)
Logs entry to a method.

Parameters:
params - The parameters to the method.
Troublesome:
Use of varargs results in array creation which can be a substantial portion of no-op case. LogMF/LogSF provides several overrides to avoid vararg except in edge cases. (RG) LogMF and LogSF implement these in LogXF which calls logger.callAppenders. callAppenders is part of the implementation and cannot be used by the API. Adding more methods here and in AbstractLogger is sufficient.

void error(Marker marker,
           String message,
           Object... params)
Logs a message with parameters at the ERROR level.

Parameters:
marker - the marker data specific to this log statement.
message - the message to log; the format depends on the message factory.
params - parameters to the message.
See Also:
getMessageFactory()
Troublesome:
Likely to misinterpret existing log4j client code that intended to call info(Object,Throwable). Incurs array creation expense on every call. (RG) I assume you meant error, not info. It isn't possible to be misinterpreted as the previous method is for that signature. Methods should be added to avoid varargs for 1, 2 or 3 parameters.

Troublesome:
Likely to misinterpret existing log4j client code that intended to call info(Object,Throwable). Incurs array creation expense on every call. (RG) It isn't possible to be misinterpreted as the previous method is for that signature. Methods should be added to avoid varargs for 1, 2 or 3 parameters.
